This paper deals with the analysis of translated texts, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The most relevant sub-category for this paper is likely to be cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to automatically reconstruct phylogenetic language trees, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of large datasets, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the use of deep learning models for the analysis of translated texts could also classify this paper under cs.DL (Deep Learning).
